 arestricted accessuhttp://purl.org/coar/access_right/c_16ecfonline access with authorization2star  aFeaturing the work of more than fifty poets writing across the last eight decades, Only the Road / Solo el Camino is the most complete bilingual anthology of Cuban poetry available to an English readership. It is distinguished by its stylistic breadth and the diversity of its contributors, who come from throughout Cuba and its diaspora and include luminaries, lesser-known voices, and several Afro-Cuban and LGBTQ poets. Nearly half of the poets in the collection are women. Only the Road paints a full and dynamic picture of modern Cuban life and poetry, highlighting their unique features and idiosyncrasies, the changes across generations, and the ebbs and flows between repression and freedom following the Revolution. Poet Margaret Randall, who translated each poem, contributes extensive biographical notes for each poet and a historical introduction to twentieth-century Cuban poetry.   aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 25. Nov 2020) 0aCuban poetryy20th centuryxTranslations into English. 0aCuban poetryy20th century. 0aCuban poetryy21st centuryxTranslations into English. 0aCuban poetryy21st century. 7aPOETRY / Anthologies (multiple authors).2bisacsh1 aRandall, Margaret1 aRandall, Margaret, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDUK Complete eBook-Package 2016z978311070808040uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9780822373858zCo-access DOI >> click Walter de Gruyter40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780822373858423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9780822373858.jpg  a978-3-11-070808-0  DUK Complete eBook-Package 2016b2016  aEBA_DUK_ALL  aEBA_DUK_EALL  aEBA_DUK_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles